title: Independent Candidate Yousaf Khan wins NA-36 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Independent candidate, Yousaf Khan has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-36, Hangu-cum-Orakzai by securing 73,076 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam Pakistan candidate, Obaidullah who bagged 34,324 votes.
The votersâ€™ turn-out remained 24.62%.
